Feature: cur list shows skills in the central repository
  `cur list` prints all skills and their versions from
  ~/.curriculum/repository/. The latest version is marked with *.

  Image: curriculum-test:latest

  Background:
    Given environment variable "CURRICULUM_HOME" is set to "/smoko-work/ch"

  Scenario: shows available skills
    Given a file "ch/repository/my-skill/1.0.0/SKILL.md" with content:
      ---
      name: my-skill
      description: "A test skill"
      ---
    When I run "cur list"
    Then exit code is 0
    Then output contains "my-skill"
    Then output contains "1.0.0"

  Scenario: marks the latest version with *
    Given a file "ch/repository/my-skill/1.0.0/SKILL.md" with content:
      ---
      name: my-skill
      description: "A test skill"
      ---
    Given a file "ch/repository/my-skill/2.0.0/SKILL.md" with content:
      ---
      name: my-skill
      description: "A test skill"
      ---
    When I run "cur list"
    Then exit code is 0
    Then output contains "2.0.0 *"
    Then output does not contain "1.0.0 *"

  Scenario: shows message when repository is empty
    When I run "cur list"
    Then exit code is 0
    Then output contains "No skills in repository"
